cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.CR 

This paper is primarily focused on improving the performance of face detection, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also proposes a new Expected Max Overlapping (EMO) score, which is a theoretical concept that can be applied to various machine learning models, making it relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses network architectures and runtime speed, which are relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) and cryptography and security (cs.CR) subcategories.
